ing and pasting to other forums.  If there are other popular forum styles you'd like supported just let me know.</p></div></div><div class="small-12 columns"><div class="panel callout"><h3>Friday, August 18 2016</h3><h5>Public workouts</h5><p>You can now set your profile to public, and share your workouts.  A <b>share</b> button will appear on your workouts if you change your profile to public.</p></div></div><div class="small-12 columns"><div class="panel callout"><h3>Wednesday, August 17 2016</h3><h5>Validations work</h5><p>You should now be able to validate your account.  Once you do that you should have five (5) invites you can send. Tell your friends!</p></div></div><div class="small-12 columns"><div class="panel callout"><h3>Tuesday, August 16 2016</h3><h5>Activity editing</h5><p>You can now see your list of activities and add new ones, add new aliases or promote one of the aliases to the "main" activity.  Go check it out!</p></div></div><div class="small-12 columns"><div class="panel callout"><h3>Monday, August 15 2016</h3><h5>We've launched!</h5><p>Welcome to lift.zone!  We've just launched, and invite codes are slowly rolling out to those that asked for them.</p><p>Currently the <b>validate</b> email isn't sending. We're waiting for our email service to be promoted out of sandbox mode.  Once that's done you can validate your account. Sorry this didn't get done before launch.</p><p>Right now all that you can do is log workouts and look up past workouts.  Coming soon: Sharing workouts with others, and editing your activity names (this will allow you to free-form type in aliases for activities rather than relying on the 'suggestions' dialog in the new workout page.</p><p>Please let me know if anything is still not working, or confusing. I'll do my best to clarify and bugfix, as I have time.</p><p>Happy lifting!</p><div class="right">--Gar</div></div></div></div></section></div><div class="row"><hr/><div class="left"><dl data-hook="navigation" class="sub-nav"><